-- Onur Air of Turkey Plans to Sell Majority Stake, Vatan Says
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-07-30T10:41:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-30/onur-air-of-turkey-plans-to-sell-majority-stake-vatan-says.html
Onur Havayollari Tasimacilik AS, a
Turkish low-cost carrier known as Onur Air, plans to sell a
majority stake and investors from Lebanon and Qatar are
interested,  Vatan  reported, without saying where it got the
information.  Cankut Bagana, who owns the Istanbul-based airline company,
hired an investment bank to manage the sale process, the
newspaper said. Onur Air has 34 Airbus aircraft in its fleet and
flies to 83 destinations in Turkey and  Europe , according to its
 website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 